data: Having entered The Lodge the day before, the housemates talk about what roles they want to play.
During a dance class, Kitten walked out and threatened to leave because she did not want to play Dandini.
The housemates had a lesson from "dame coach" Dave Lynn and later had the first script read through with Chris and Ruth.

The housemates appeared live on T4 and Jade and Anouska auditioned for the role of Cinderella. The lines for who played Cinderella were then open from 11.30am to 6pm. Having previously complained about the script, Narinder talked with the writer Jonathan Harvey in the Great Hall.
The housemates spent the day rehearsing.
The housemates returned to The Lodge. Later the housemates ran through Cinderella in full costume and had a singing lesson.
During a full day of rehearsals, Kitten walked out of rehearsals and threatened to leave. However, she later returned.
The housemates spent the day rehearsing. At 9pm, they performed Cinderella live on E4 and later left the house.

table-0122-442.caption: List of major dam failures
data: Defective construction, small leak in wall grew until dam failed.

Lax regulations and cost cutting lead to an insufficient design, which fell apart when the reservoir was full. 600 million gallons of water were released, wiping out 4 towns and making national headlines. This dam break lead to increased regulation of dam construction.
Heavy snow and rain following public calls by the dam's chief engineer to strengthen the earthen structure.
Heavy flooding coupled with poor foundation quality
Poor design, use of dynamite to remedy structural problems.
Construction flaws caused the dam failure
Heavy rains caused the dam to give way. Dam was later rebuilt in the 1960s
Contractor blamed cost-cutting in construction but 25" of rain had fallen in preceding 5 days. This was the last dam failure to cause death in the UK to date (2013).

Geological instability of canyon wall that could not have been detected with available technology of the time, combined with human error that assessed developing cracks as "normal" for a dam of that type.
Geological unstable base combined with flood.
Geological fault possibly enhanced by explosives work during construction; initial geo-study was not thorough.
Dam wall burst due to pressue of accumulated rain water.

A tailings dam at Plakalnitsa copper mine near the city of Vratsa failed. A total 450,000 cu m of mud and water inundated Vratsa and the nearby village of Zgorigrad, which suffered widespread damage. The official death toll is 107, but the unofficial estimate is around 500 killed.
Flooding, dam outlets flooded with debris.
Extreme rainfall beyond the planned design capability of the dam. Worst dam failure.
Water leakage through earthen wall, leading to dam failure.
Heavy rainfall and flooding that over-topped the dam.
Unknown, possibly design error as dam was raised several times by owners to improve power generation.
Heavy rain and flooding beyond spillway capacity.
Flooding beyond discharge and storage capacity damaged the main dam and destroyed the secondary dam in the scheme.
Outlet pipe erosion; dam under-maintained due to location
Poor maintenance and low margin for error in design; outlet pipes failed leading to pressure on dam.
Lightning struck power system, turbines shut down. Water rose behind dam while trying to restart. Backup power systems failed, could not raise spillway gates in time. Dam overtopped(rebuilt).

Problems started after two weeks of constant rain, which severely engorged soils, rivers and reservoirs. Post-flood enquiries discovered that the network of dikes and dams protecting the city was poorly maintained.
Design and construction deficiencies resulted in failure in heavy icing conditions
Heavy rain during construction caused failure, dam was later completed
Peat dam became lighter than water during droughts and floated away
Heavy rains caused earthen dam and bank to wash away
A small hole in the dam grew and eventually led to failure
Poor maintenance. 3000 people homeless. A second failure happened 11 days after.
Sudden and extreme flooding caused by abnormally severe rain
Heavy rain and flooding. Several possible specific factors to include poor maintenance, lack of inspection and illegal modifications.
Heavy rain. The flood affected over 2.3 million people in the northern part of Bihar.
Collapses when turbine 2 broke apart violently, flooding the turbine hall and causing the ceiling to collapse.
Poor maintenance and heavy monsoon rain
Failure of concrete impound wall on alumina plant tailings dam.
Failed after a period of flooding. 4000 people displaced.
Failed after a period of heavy snowmelt. A crack in the dam went un-repaired for years. Eight people killed and several communities flooded.
A gate in the diversion tunnel broke after a period of heavy rain during the reservoir's first filing. The accident killed ten workers.
